description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/4959/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'operation, liquid manure storage and processing facility', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of 'operation, liquid manure storage and processing facility' of 1 m3. It includes use of infrastructure (storage facility) and electricity necessary to agitate 1 m3 of manure. 

This activity starts with the service generation.


This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
